{"lemma":"مِلَّةُ","slug":"مِلَّةُ","root":"م.ل.ل","root_slug":"م-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مِلَّة","root":"ملل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":15},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43676","n43679","n43680"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tedium, weariness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bread baked in hot ashes"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sweating, fever"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tacking stitch, basting stitch, large stitch"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"frame for laying something on top, bedstead","tags":["Egypt"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ideological or religious community, philosophy, creed, weltanschauung, religion, denomination."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived or cognate to Aramaic מִלָּה (mellā, “word, speech, statement; matter or case, logic, reason, rationale; exposition; consensus”); compare Classical Syriac ܡܠܬܐ (mellṯā). Connected natively to the root م ل ء (m l ʔ) meaning “an adult who is regarded for his opinion”, “the affluent, nobles, or decision-makers in a tribe”, “to speak about or discuss”, “an assembly where consultation and opinions are given”, “expressing disdain or scorn”, “to give a critique”, “to converse or to give a review”, “to give your take on a situation”, “to give one's judgment or input”. See also the potentially derived root م ي ل (m y l) meaning “leaning, one's leaning” and the Millat Ibrahim, the critique, philosophy, or ideology of the prophet Ibrahim, namely Monotheism."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43676","headword_ar":"مَلَّهُ","root":"ml","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely bread, or flesh-meat,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into hot ashes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to bake, or roast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, &c.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mal~a Alv~awoba","text_ar":"مَلَّ الثَّوْبَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sewed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tacked, the garment, or piece of cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slightly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"previously to the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stronger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sewing termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkaf~","text_ar":"الكَفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$al~a","text_ar":"شَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malilotuhu","text_ar":"مَلِلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malilotu Eanohu","text_ar":"مَلِلْتُ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was avers from it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loathed it; was disgusted by it, with it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was weary of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned"},{"kind":"page_break","n":3023},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away from it with disgust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say^ima","text_ar":"سَيِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mal~a malAaluka","text_ar":"مَلَّ مَلاَلُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May thy disgust pass away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cease"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDal~a A@ll~`hu DalaAlaka","text_ar":"اَضَلَّ ا@للّٰهُ ضَلَالَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43679","headword_ar":"مَلَّةٌ","root":"ml","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hollow that is made for baking bread: or the hot dust and ashes"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the bread is baked"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hot ashes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ashes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, in which fire is kindled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbz","text_ar":"خبز"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubozu mal~apK","text_ar":"خُبْزُ مَلَّةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bread baked in hot ashes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [It is generally made in the form of thick round cakes.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n43680","headword_ar":"مِلَّةٌ","root":"ml","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A religion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way of belief and practice in respect of religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, &c.) ―         -b2-  See 8."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}